author: @sonalisamal2009
text:
This is a fun song and MV. It's the song that you can make anyone dance to. It's all about having fun. This song is an anthem. It's iconic and evergreen. ❤

This is the second K-pop song I've heard in my life, after 'Gangnam style' by PSY. And, the funny yet sad part is I didn't even know the name of this song, or that it was a K-pop song. I had no clue about Seventeen at all, back then. I had heard a part of this song (the title line) numerous times in different places- game shows on TV, and other contests, but I had no clue about the name of the song or the artiste. I hadn't even explored. This year I started listening to K-pop and 'Super' was my first Seventeen song after knowing about them, and the beginning of my journey as a Carat. Then I started listening to all of Seventeen's songs and when I heard 'Aju nice', I was so happy and excited. It felt like coming back to something that was meant for you. So, my happiness as a Carat grew even more. It's the same feeling of having a best friend in kindergarten who you get separated from in childhood and have no contact with or clue about, but suddenly meet again in your adult years. 'Aju nice' is that song for me. The fact that I found Seventeen when I was going through a low time, and when I needed them makes my belief even stronger that I was meant to be here. So, this is a forever for me. ♾️ Seventeen will be my always. ❤

author: @armymoagenenctzenarohacara6930
text:
I will just drop it here..... 
It's a story of 2020 when I was struck by the hallyu wave and started to stan groups... My friend introduced me to seventeen and I wasn't actually interested to stan them or any other group at that time but boom, she forced me to watch this mv and not gonna lie, I did love this song and mv at the first place but when she asked I asked I will think about it. After 3 days she was shocked to know that I even memorised their names and watched atleast 4 - 5 songs of them. I said thank you for introducing me to them, I am not gonna leave.... 
Now, when I think about it, I am glad she forced me to watch otherwise my life would have been useless.... 
Technically this is my first seventeen mv and I got shocked to know that this didn't win on any music shows but still no one can deny it's iconic af.....

How to stream when you have a wifi?

1. Make a list of what we need to stream.

3. Loop

5. Repeat again.

STREAMING IS EASY WHEN YOU HAVE WIFI. PERIOD. PERIODISM. PERIODIC. PERIODICAL.

text:
No sé si es divertido o triste que el mv no tenga más vistas aún cuando la canción es tan pegajosa y suena en todas partes, como mínimo el coro es tarareado por algunos conductores en programas de variedades cuando se da la ocasión. Y Carat sabe demasiado bien lo mucho que los chicos se divierten con su propia canción al final de los conciertos. Dieron tantos buenos recuerdos a todos los que pudieron asistir en sus giras, y aún así éste MV no tiene las views suficientes después de cinco años de debut.

De verdad podemos hacerlo mejor.💗

A quien pueda traducir éste comentario en su idioma sea libre de hacerlo. Hay que motivarnos, Carat, para cumplir los sueños de éstos chicos maravillosos.💗

CARAT & SEVENTEEN FIGHTING~

author: @kimmemegyutheclumsypuppy7762
text:
[NEW CARAT STARTER PACK !!!]  =>Names, Basic informations ... 
=> please like this comment so people can see it ;D ! (thanks ♥)


So as you know this group is called "Seventeen". They debuted on the 26th of May 2015 with the track called "Adore U". 

They are composed of 13 members and are known as "auto-producing idols" because they do on their own songs/choreographies/production. 
To make this task easier, they can split into 3 teams: Vocal Team, Performance Team (Dance making), Hip Hop Team (Rap)

Also Seventeen's fandom is "Carats" as a reference to their first song called "Shining Diamond" : 
They are our diamond and as the number of Carats increase, the diamond gets more precious ;) ! Moreover in this song, they say "You can't imitate Seventeen Carat" and it's a reference of the special link there is between Seventeen and their fans (It's actually more like a big family relationship than a idol-fan one :3)

So here an introduction to the members:


[VOCAL TEAM: The vocalists of the band]

0:04 : DK (1997): Vocal
0:20 : Seungkwan (1998): Vocal
0:33 : Joshua (1996): Vocal
1:51 : Woozi (1996): Vocal, Vocal Team Leader, Producer/Composer
2:09 : Jeonghan (1995): Vocal


[PERFORMANCE TEAM: they all create the choreographies for Seventeen's albums]

0:11 : Hoshi (1996):  Dancer, Performance Team Leader
1:03 : Dino (1999): Dancer, Maknae
1:10 : The8 (1997): Dancer, China Line
1:13 : Jun (1996): Dancer, China Line


[HIP HOP TEAM: Rap]

0:15 : Wonwoo (1996):  Rapper
0:59 : Vernon (1998): Rapper
2:01 : S.Coups (1995): Rapper, Hip Hop Team Leader, Seventeen Leader
2:17 : Mingyu (1997): Rapper, Visual


Also if you have troubles to remember their names you can't watch the following shows ;D:
  -> "Seventeen Project": It's the story of how they went from pre-debut to debut (it's really moving but awesome :3)
  -> "One Fine Day - 13 Castaways Boys": Their first OFD and it's funnnnnyyyy as hell xDDD ! #MustWatch
  -> "Star Show 360
  -> Weekly Idol
  -> "One Fine Day in Japan - 13 Boys Tycoon Vacations": Their 2nd OFD is currently broadcasted each friday at 
                                                                                                     19:00 KST until the end of May  :)


Hope it'll help ;DD !!
If you have any further question Carats are here to answer :3 !

author: @kyla2033
text: EXO is my ultimate bias group and I know they will be for as long as they're promoting but no one has captured my attention since 2012 as much as Seventeen has :') They're a bunch of incredibly talented boys who produce their own music, choreograph their own dances, write their own lyrics and each and every single one of them harbour different but refreshing personalities that make it impossible not to pay attention to them. They worked so hard for this recognition and they deserve all of it and more. I came to their concert not knowing too much about them at all (I only started getting to know Seventeen a couple of weeks back and their concert for me was on the 30th of August) but I left feeling like a hardcore stan; their passion for music reeked in all performances and their stage presence was nothing short of amazing. I've only watched all of their lives and a few of their shows, but my heart swells at how much they love what they do. My broke ass can afford another group to wholly support x #STANSEVENTEEN

author: @seanieboi1234
text: This makes me so proud to be a CARAT. They are truly unique out of other groups. Their music just makes you have a lot of emotions, but overall they just wanna produce catchy music that everyone can enjoy, male or female, young or old. Other Kpop groups always try to do stuff that are trending, like being fierce or very cute. Im not saying that is a bad thing, but Seventeen just found that balance, and you see that through their albums. Plus, the chemistry with all members is so genuine!!! There is barely any awkward moments between each member. And of course, they are hard working, doung their own choreo and songs. Now, im not bashing other groups. All groups do work hard, and we should support them too, but Seventeen is a group that has a lot of heart, a lot of joy, and a lot of talent!!! Good Job Seventeen and all your hard work and catchy music. love seeing you guys grow!!!

author: @dainnahsaur
text: Okay tbh I'm into a lot of groups and I've stumbled upon seventeen about a week ago, and I've never been a hardcore fan since EXO and watching all of seventeen's interviews, variety shows, etc., they are so talented and under appreciated ! Like Woozi produced and writes all their songs, Hoshi choreographs their dances, and they get help from other members too and I think that's really great. I'm just so shocked at how this group is so amazing and under appreciated with all their talents and skills ! They're slowly climbing up my ultimate bias group list (my ult bias group is EXO) And to see that this group isn't as acknowledged compared to other groups makes me sad because they work so hard !! (Not that other groups don't work hard, they work hard too) But in my opinion seventeen got popular real fast by both their team work and hard work. It's just that in my perspective, seventeen work the hardest. (Please don't bash me it's just an opinion >.<) Plus I'm a hardcore minghao stan ~

author: @ThreeHeartBullets
text:
I don't know if all of you know about the YHY sketchbook incident, so I will briefly talk about it. YHY Sketchbook has a "no photography/ videography" policy. Seventeen just went for their Sketchbook recording and fansites were caught taking photos and videos. Even after warning, and even Seungkwan saying, "please do not take photos anymore, please", fansites continue taking photos and videos till the end of the recording. Some angry YHY Sketchbook audience even left the studio because of those fansite photographers. Seventeen looked really gloomy after their recording and carats were warned that if any breaching of rules happen on KBS shows again, carats or even Seventeen might be banned from the shows. Some carats even claimed that this incident has affect Seventeen's Sketchbook showtime and their Music Bank score. 
Tbh, I think this is a very big warning for Carats. We have been known to be a very friendly fandom but with our fandom rapidly expanding and fans getting more proactive since our boys are becoming more popular, I think there is a need for all Carats to be more careful and reign in our excitement when necessary. This incident not only reflects badly on Carats, but on Seventeen as well, because Carats represent Seventeen. I hope all Carats, by it kCarats or iCarats, can spread awareness on this issue. Seventeen and Carats have also been in many fanwars and scandals recently and I just hope everyone can keep calm and love Seventeen!! It's okay what other people say, but we have to protect Seventeen, by not making things worse and just support them with all our might. Thanks!! 
PLEASE, IF YOU DO SEE FANSITES POSTING YHY SKETCHBOOK PHOTOS, PLEASE TALK ABOUT THE INCIDENT. DO NOT SPREAD THE PHOTOS, AND DO TELL FANSITES TO TAKE DOWN THE PHOTOS!! THANKS!!

author: @stanthenationshoe6127
text:
*I'm so fucking mad.*
Long rant ahead

So Seventeen have this sketchbook performance right? And you guys know that taking pictures/videos aren't allowed right? Apparently, these immature carats broke the rules and Seventeens performance got cancelled. *Got fucking cancelled* Guess who was scolded and punished? Seventeen. Fucking Seventeen got scolded because of their fans. The most depressing thing about this is that even our Boo fucking Seungkwan *begged* them to stop. This is what the fans who were there heard what Seungkwan said..

*"Please don't take any pictures.. Please don't"*

That person who posted it even said Boo had this desperate expression. You would think they (the fans) would stop right? No they fucking didn't. They still took pictures until the end of the show. Some of the audiences even left because they were mad. What made me angry is the fact that they had to fcking beg. To their fans. You know how they love us right? They even worked their asses off to get this opportunity but the fans ruined it. Theres pictures of them going home from the show in tumblr or instagram if you want to see it but holy crap, they look so sad. I'm so disappointed.

*Edit*: I just found out that they even brought cookies to the show for the fans and their Music bank broadcasting point were deducted. Now they have less chances of winning and their cookies are wasted.

author: @marivink1281
text:
HEY HELLO THERE? DID YOU FALL? SLIP? DOVE? OR MAYBE SOMEONE PUSHED YOU IN. ARE YOU FROM ANOTHER FANDOM AND ARE CURIOUS? EITHER WAY IF YOU WANNA KNOW ABOUT THE DIAMOND LIFE LET ME EXPLAIN AND SIT BACK LOVE.

Fan made Guide for New Carats~

Seventeen is a 13 membered boy band, you might see 12 during the dancing cuts but one member is currently ill and the company along with the rest of the members are putting his health first however he is in the MV. If you're curious about the name 13 member + 3 Units + 1 Team. 

As you can tell Seventeen is one of the largest kpop bands out there currently but that way the bands has more charms to express. Although a usual band usually has one leader Seventeen indeed does have one general Leader but they also have a leader for each unit meaning 3 leaders in total. 

Their symbol of friends are rings they wear on their pinkies.

The three Units are Hip Hop, Vocal, and Performance.
Weird Member Description

S.Coups (Choi Seungcheol) August 8, 1995 <Leo> 
Seventeen's leader, dad, eldest member, and Hip Hope Unit Leader. He has a tough yet kind image. However he's actually an adorable puppy who also wants you're attention. He watches out for the members and relaxes them for performances. They make fun of his stage name sometimes with Me Gustas Tu the members switch it to S.Coups Tu
Unit: Hip Hop
Where you can find him in the MV 2:26
Key: Coups' ears are a bit large, well not large but his hair doesn't cover them. They're pierced too. In the MV He has a sphere silver snug piercing? I think it is. 

Jeonghan (Yoon Jeonghan) October 10, 1995 <Libra>
Seventeen's Angel. He's caled that because his name is literally pronounced Angel in Korean. Although he's an angel he's usually behind the pranks Seventeen has and he cheats on the members (When it comes to shippings) Usually looks and has better hair than most girls. There was poll for an idol who could pull of the bob hair cut the most and he beat all the women, and won that pull with at least 50% of the votes.
Unit: Vocal
Where you can find him in the MV 1:23
Key: His long hair. He's hairs short currently but he usually has the longest hair out of all the members. 

Joshua (Hong Jisoo) December 30, 1995 <Capricorn> (Same Birthday as V from BTS ayyy) 
Seventeen's gentlemen, he's known to be very charismatic, very well mannered, and has a gentle voice. He's a polite boy. But don't let that fool you he actually is very silly and talks a lot~ He's from LA and is fluent in English. Many Carats make memes out of him for some reason lol. If you hear a carat saying "Jisoo Christ" it's because Joshua is actually a christian so he's a "pure" boy. But this man is dangerous he's a major bias wrecker if he isn't already your bias.
Unit: Vocal
Where you can find him in the MV 1:24 and 0:34
Key: Joshua has a Helix/Cartilage piercing that's usually a cross. He has cat like eyes.

Jun (Wen Junhui/Moon Junhwi) June 10, 1996 <Gemini>
I don't know why but he comes off as a greasy character. He's in charge of being cool and handsome apparently and knows he's good looking. He mixes martial arts into his dancing sometimes. He's 1/2 of the China Line, master of eye-rolling when the members do something stupid. Sometimes comes off unappreciated (Not enough Stans put him out there??) But he can become a bias wrecker, many say this is his Era
Unit: Performance
Where you can find him in the MV 1:14
Key: Needless to say he's one of the members that has his hair going in Natural colors only like brown or blonde most of the time. (Correct me if I'm wrong pls) But his nose and eyes pop out. Jun has a little dot on his cheek~

Hoshi (Kwon Soonyoung) June 15, 1996 <Gemini>
Seventeen's Performance unit leader and choreographer. A cute hyper active bubbly fluffball that can change into a hot sexy lady killer in 0.5 seconds if he wants to. No one knows how he does that Carats are still researching. He's also known as 10:10 (10 hour 10 Minute) because everyone knows his eyes are small and they point like clock hands (But we love his small eyes <3) He talks a lot. 1/3 of Seventeen's gag trio.
Unit: Performance
Where you can find him in the MV 1:28
Key: His eyes. Even if aren't "small" (Bro eyeliner makes him so kwute) you can't miss him!

Wonwoo (Jeon Wonwoo) July 17, 1996 <Cancer>
Seventeen's Emo member. Just kiddin' he usually very calm though and has a sexy resting face according to the members. He's also the one who's currently ill since he has acute gastritis. Members are watching out for him though. I don't mention ships much but he's a packaged with Mingyu. It's hard to NOT stan both of them cause they are a pack. They're called Meanie. Wonwoo was given the nickname Mr. Beanie Predebut so combine that with Mingyu and you get Meanie.
Unit: Hip Hop
Where you can find him in the MV 0:15
Key: He's one of the tall members, sometimes he wears piercings, but the biggest fact is that his face is usually calm. Most of the most. A lot.

Woozi (Lee Jihoon) November 22, 1996 <Sagittarius>
Seventeen's Composer/Producer, and Vocal Unit Leader. You might think Woozi is an adorable smol bean. Very kwute you know...YEAH THIS KID IS SATAN. You might hear something like that from his stans. And it's true. Carat rule: Don't mess with Woozi. He's the shortest member yes but he's one of the Hyungs as well. He's cute yeah but he beats of the members sometimes and hit Mingyu with his guiltar once. Aegyo is not his thing, even though his looks fit it he just can't nope. He's pretty calm himself members nicknamed him a documentary because of that. Woozi's like 5'4 fyi.
Unit: Vocal
Where you can find him in the MV 1:53
Key: Smallest member you literally can't miss him. His eyes are a bit small too and his hair is ususally down. (Exceptions are in Adore U and his bedhead)

DK aka Dokyeom (Lee Seokmin) Febuary 18, 1997 <Aquarius>
Seventeen's Main Vocal and Speaker phone. He's also a happy virus that's part of BooSoonSeok their gag trio. His Smile so wide and cute it's going to make you smile. He's very cute looking but can also be hot if he wants too. He's usually teasing Seungkwan or making Jokes with Hoshi. He and Vernon also share the same Birthday~
Unit: Vocal
Where you can find him in the MV 2:43
Key: He has a long slender face and an impressive jawline. His nose is kinda sharp.

Mingyu (Kim Mingyu) April 6, 1997 <Aries>
Seventeen's Visual  and Tallest Member. He's so tall this boi what is now like 6'1? Literally a man that can do it all. He can be cute, hot, fix things, and cook. I mean it he can cook like go watch ONE FINE DAY, he and Dk literally make all the meals for the members. He also eats the most. He's always sneezing or is caught doing spreading his germs. Once he sneezed and wiped it on Vernon when he wasn't looking. But overall he's a giraffe Puppy. Wonwoo's housewife.
Unit: Hip Hop
Where you can find him in the MV 0:18
Key: Tallest member, pretty lips, He has fangs actually and it's so attractiveeeeee. 

The8 (Xu Minghao/Seo Myung Ho) November 7, 1997 <Scorpio>
Their adorable adorable fairy. He cleans the dorms when the members don't I believe. This boy's always experimenting with his hair he died it cotton candy once and even permed his hair to make it look like ramen. He's is cute yeah but he's also a little savage like Woozi he just doesn't express it as much as Woozi does. He's a Chinese Member of Seventeen and can kill you with one dance. He's a B-boy and I mean he slays when it comes to dancing.
Unit: Performance
Where you can find him in the MV 1:11
Key: His ears are pierced and he wears two earrings the majority of time, his nose is quite large and his eyes are big too.

Seungkwan (Boo Seungkwan) January 16, 1998 <Capricorn>
IT'S YOUR BOI BOO. Because listen, No matter what member you stan, no matter what. He's going to make you laugh. He's literally Seventeen's Sass Machine, he's a variety star in the making. Despite that his vocals are literally on point. He's always extra but he's Seventeen's main vocal he hit four octaves in their song Pretty U.You gotta love dis boi.
Unit: Vocal
Where you can find him in the MV 0:26
Key: Boo has a cute lil dot above his lips and he's really skinny but chubbs cute compared to the other members.

Vernon (Choi Hansol) Febuary 18, 1998 <Aquarius>
Seventeen's Leonardo Dicaprio. He's also known as Memesol since fans usually snap shot his face at the worst of times and put random captions. He's Half Caucasian and is Half Korean. He and Seungkwan have a little joke thing going around it's cute. As Seungkwan raps Vernon Sings lol. To him his fans are his girlfriends~
Unit: Hip Hop
Where you can find him in the MV 0:58
Key: You can just tell. I'd have to say he has cute big brown eyes.

Dino (Lee Chan) Febuary 11, 1999 <Aquarius>
Here's where younger fans come in. One of the youngest Idols in the Kpop industry. He's also the Maknae of the group. Members tease him because of that and treat him the their lil bro they must protect. He out grew Woozi but he's still the second shortest. Carats may refer to him as pure sometimes cause he literally gets happy about being able to stay awake over the weekend. He's very confident and his name yes literally comes from Dinosaur. He's refered as the small giant Maknae so kwute. He loves Micheal Jackson.
Unit: Performance
Where you can find him in the MV 1:04
Key: Dino's eyes area bit small and his lips are very thin.

I recommend you actually watching their MV Mansae to get to know these boys better. Their visual are really different from each other than in NICE the song is great too

author: @PureeCharm
text:
Since a lot of people want to get into SVT because of this MV, let me tell you more about them! :D

0:04 
That's Dokyeom (DK). His real name is Lee Seokmin. He smiles A LOT and he's really cheerful. Beautiful thighs. Goes on radio shows a lot with Seungkwan. His voice is very strong and powerful. Great cook. Part of the vocal unit.

0:11
That's Hoshi. His real name is Kwon Soonyoung. Hoshi nicknamed himself ''10:10'' because his eyes slant up like the hands on a clock when its 10:10. He makes a lot of puns and the members never laugh lmao. He's a very cute squishy bun but he's in charge of sexy dancing in SVT. He's the leader of the performance unit, and he choreographs all of their songs. Very talented dancer and choreographer. He says ''Naega Hosh'' (I'm Hoshi) in Korean. We don't know why, he's just weird but we love him. Leader of the Performance Unit.

0:16
That's Wonwoo. His real name is Jeon Wonwoo. Wonwoo is the very quiet member of SVT, he doesn't show a lot of facial emotion either so we call him emo. He likes reading a lot and gets excited when talking about books. He's quiet but if you talk to him he smiles really widely and jokes around. His jokes are also really bad like Hoshi (he tries). He got nicknamed SVT's ''bag of luck'' on the show One Fine Day. But in a game, he got the lowest points and everyone died laughing because it was really ironic. Deepest voice in SVT. Wonwoo is actually sick at the moment with acute gastritis, that's the reason why he wasn't dancing. He'll heal quickly but he still needs to rest so he won't be promoting with the group until he's 100% better. He still participated in making the album and the MV.  Part of the Hip Hop Unit.

0:17
That's Mingyu. His real name is Kim Mingyu. This boy is talented beyond words. He can cook, clean fish, make chicken, clean, he is just husband material. He is the tallest member in SVT (185cm I think). We call him MingEW because he sneezes or coughs into his hands a lot. Very beautiful man. Part of the Hip Hop Unit.

0:20
That's Seungkwan. His real name is Boo Seungkwan. This boy is really something else. He is so hyper all the time and he's the best at MCing and being on variety shows. He loves his mom a lot and cries when he sees her. Actually Seungkwan is the crybaby of the group, he's emotional but that's why we love him. He has lovely chubby cheeks but a skinny body. He's a talented singer, he can always hit the high notes. Part of the Vocal Unit.

0:34
That's Joshua. His real name is Hong Joshua/Jisoo. He's full Korean but he was raised in America and got scouted. At first look, Joshua is the member with the pretty face and the soft voice and plays acoustic guitar. But if you look a little more, he's one of the funniest members without trying. It's like, you don't expect him to make a joke, but when he does, it's freakin' hilarious. He does this thing where he falls on one of his legs, spins around, and gets back up. The members always get excited when this happens. He was inspired by a lot of Youtube artists who made covers and sang. He is part of the Vocal Unit.

0:53
That's Vernon. His real name is Chwe Hansol/Vernon. Meme. He's got that natural swag, you know? Like if someone talks to him he's like ''whats up man'' or ''yo.'' Joshua does this a lot too. Vernon get's really into the music and when he's on stage. If he's about to laugh, he sort of purses his lips and raises one eyebrow and then grins really widely. A lot of musicians said they were impressed by him the most in the group because of his stage presence and natural rapping. Part of the Hip Hop Unit.

0:54
That's Dino. His real name is Lee Chan. He's the maknae. Dino is OBSESSED with Michael Jackson. If you give Dino any song with a choreo, he can change the choreo into Michael Jackson ver. Gets really happy when you compliment him. He gets asked a lot ''who's baby are you?'' In which he replies ''Jeonghans baby...'' in a really sick-of-your-shit way. Part of Performance Unit.

1:11
That's The8. His real name is Xu Minghao. He's Chinese. He's not very good at Korean yet since he's only been there for 2 years or so; he has a really thick accent and the members say he's cute when he messes up in his speaking. He's cute now and does a lot of aegyo but when he was younger he used to take pictures as if he was a gangster and really serious-looking. We call him thughao. If you make him mad, he won't be hesitant to defend himself which is unlike Koreans. But he gets along really well with all the members. Part of Performance Unit.

1:14. That's Jun. His real name is Wen Junhui. He's Chinese. He's very close with Minghao and he helps translating for him. We call him the prince of China because he is just amazing. He cares about his image and acts really sexy sometimes. Unfortunately, a lot of people don't give him attention, please bias this man! He doesn't speak a lot, but when he does he has this sort of deep voice that's boyish at the same time. He was an actor ever since he was a child. Part of Performance Unit.

1:23
That's Jeonghan. His real name is Yoon Jeonghan. His nickname is angel since he's so pretty with long hair, but he can be a devil when he wants to. He likes pranking the members but cares for them a lot and cried when Wonwoo got sick. He's the one who's always babying Dino. Pretty in anything and everything. Soft voice but can also be powerful. Part of Vocal Unit.

1:52
That's Woozi. His real name is Lee Jihoon. He's the composer for SVT, and he makes and writes the songs for their albums. He admits that he feels pressure to do well but his songs are always great. He doesn't joke around a lot and is generally serious but if he finds something funny, he laughs with his mouth wide open. Is the cutest member because he's the shortest but he hates doing aegyo. Very talented singer. Leader of the Vocal Unit.

2:02
That's S.Coups. His real name is Choi Seungcheol. He is the perfect leader for SVT. He is ALWAYS looking out for the members and always listens to them if they have a problem. He loves sports and he's the strongest, so they nicknamed him hulcoups. Some say he is the father of SVT and Jeonghan is the mother of SVT. He's very handsome with a beautiful jawline and lovely thighs. Can get scary but he's never mean and he tries to lighten up the member's moods and make everyone cheerful. He is the General Leader and the Leader of the Hip Hop Unit.

If you want to get to know more about SVT, I suggest watching Seventeen Project. It's a show where their company tests them to see if they're ready to debut and face the public as idols. Can get emotional at times. (All the episodes are subbed on Youtube). 
You should also watch One Fine Day. It's hilarious, they get castaway on an island in Korea and they need to fish and make their own food. (All the episodes are subbed on Youtube). 

If you need anymore information, look up at some of the fansites dedicated to SVT. They have a fanbase since pre-debut because they had an online show called 17TV where a camera would watch them do their everyday practices. 

Please don't steal this, I worked really hard on it.

If you're becoming a fan of SVT and slipping into the diamond life, we welcome you! Our fandom name is Carat. Dino said that they are the diamonds but the diamond's value only increases with the amount of carats.

Dear all Carat's,
When I saw that Very Nice had reached 1M in less than a day I started tearing up. It may seem stupid to tear up over something like this, but it made me so happy knowing how hardworking this fandom is. I am in many fandoms, but the one I know I will stay in until the end is SEVENTEEN's. Carat's, you guys are so peaceful and cause no trouble for anyone, so thank you for working so hard for SEVENTEEN, and being an overall beautiful and amazing fandom. I am going to participate in helping them achieve #VeryNice1stWin. I love you guys, and I love SEVENTEEN.

author: @alhemičarka
text:
Okay I see a lot of people getting into the fandom due to this video so to wish you a warm welcome, here's the breakdown of the members (in age order). (This was all written off the top of my head and I realized I was rambling only when I was halfway through and it was too late so I apologize. If this is too much information for you to take in, look just at the stuff before the semicolons(;))

(2:01 - 2:08 (left)) S.Coups - general leader, leader of the Hip Hop Unit, main rapper; will do anything for his boys, dad, whipped for the angel, cute as hell, sometimes writes lyrics, has the booty and the thighs(Hip Hop Unit)

(1:19 - 1:24)(he doesn't sing this part tho, his part comes on later) Jeonghan - lead vocal; angel(cheonsa/1004), pretty boy, mom, has leader (and everyone else basically) wrapped around his finger, actual spawn of the devil, "Lucky Jeonghan", loves to publicly humiliate other members, expecially maknae line, but is not above using his woe ways on Seungcheol eother, will ruin your bias list at some point or another (Vocal Unit)

(0:35 - 0:38) Joshua - lead vocal; gentleman, born in America, Christian as fuck, also known as Holy Jisoos, son of the Lord, #blessed, your parents would approve of him if you brought him to family gathering, plays guitar(Vocal Unit)

(1:14 - 1:18) Jun - main dancer, sub vocal; Prince Jun, too much talent to handle, is awarded junior actor, one half of the Chinaline, has a habit of eye-fucking the camera whenever he gets the chance, hugely underappreciated, one of the most attractive guys I've ever laid my eyes on(Performance Unit)

(0:11s - 0:15) Hoshi - main dancer, leader of the Performance unit, choreographer, MC, sub vocal; has split personality - a funny, dorky one and a sexy as hell one, has a _very nice_ voice (once upon a time was part of the Vocal Unit), mastermind of choreos, moves his body like no other, we're all waiting for the day he takes his shirt off(Performance Unit)

(2:21 - 2:23 (right)) Wonwoo - lead rapper -sub vocal xD- ; adorable sloth, book worm (apparently sucker for romance), half of SVT's most infamous ship, shy but a giant dork basically(Hip Hop Unit)

(1:52 - 2:00) Woozi - lead vocal, producer, composer, arranger, leader of the Vocal Unit; most talented guy you'll ever meet(all of SVT is really), smol bean, cute as hell, will get angry if you even implicitly call him cute and chase you down with a guitar and killing intent, is precious and smol, was shit at dancing some five years ago but damn he's good now, have i mentioned he's smol?(Vocal Unit)

(0:04 - 0:10) D.K (Dokyeom) - main vocal; amazing voice, even more amazing smile, mood maker, the happy virus, can be sexy as hell if he wants _cough_ SuJu's U special stage _cough_, has legs to die for(Vocal Unit)

(0:17 - 0:19) Mingyu - lead rapper, official visual of the group; i said official cause half the members can be considered visuals(e.i Jun, Jeonghan, Vernon, S.Coups), is handsome as fuck tho, if he's not ur bias he's ur bias wrecker, the other half of SVT's most infamous ship, tall as hell, Woozi's designated piggyback ride(Hip Hop Unit)

(1:10 - 1:14) The8 - main dancer, sub rapper; precious innocent lil bub, shady as fuck tho, other half of the Chinaline, still hasn't perfected his Korean, you can't rly tell if he's judging people or trying to understand what they're saying, has a sweet ass voice that becomes surprisingly powerful when he raps(Performance Unit)

(0:20 - 0:25) Seungkwan - main vocal, MC; his voice will either make you cry or make you shiver, depending on the mood, Diva Boo(Boo is his last name), Booyonce, Boonon, wannabe rapper, aspiring emcee, will steal your heart with his cute antics and chubby cheeks( he's been losing weight recently tho ): ), will cut anyone down with his sass, supportive of the whole group even though he's in maknae line, generally savage(Vocal Unit)

(0:58 - 1:02) Vernon - main rapper, sub dancer; is one of the most handsome guys I've ever seen, half Korean half American, this boy's entire existence is basically a meme, he raps like he breathes seriously, he's really dorky, his voice is everything, when he starts rapping in english he will end you, but real talk now his reactions to everything are so funny, he's gentle and caring and really just so lovable(also Korea's Leo DiCaprio. Have you seen the comparison pics? Cause daaamn boi) (HipHop Unit)

( 0:54 - 0:58) Dino - main dancer, maknae; he might be the youngest but this boy made parts of multiple choreos, biggest Michael Jackson fanboy, seriously good dancer, cute as hell, also hot as hell when he wants and they let him to be, if you've been into kpop for a couple of years chances are he's younger than you(Performance Unit)

*-dear carats if i forgot something or you think something is wrong please correct me-*

*WELCOME TO THE DIAMOND LIFE*﻿

text:
In Mansae, there are two lines by Minghao
너라는 꽃이 피었습니다.
너라는 꽃을 바라보니까.
Trans: A flower called you has blossomed
I’m only looking at a flower called you
It's obvious that flower = you
-
In Pretty U, the last line goes:
꽃잎은 내게 어떤 답을 전해 줄까
Trans: What answer will the flower petals give me?
It's a hint saying flower petals = you
And what answer will YOU give me
-
In Very Nice's MV,
we can see the flower petals got blown up from their chest and they got blown by the flower petals too
It's actually representing heartthrob
If flower petals = you, then from Pretty U they asked what answer will YOU give
And now in Very Nice, YOU gave them heartthrob and legit blown them away

text: Okay so concept theory: They're all impressed by the girl and seem to have a strong gaze on her but when she returns the gaze they become weak and look away (like in Vernons case). She seems to have the upper hand and it's as if at her command once they boys hit they're limits, they're hearts explode. That's probably what the confetti represents being its on their left side. But they all still seem to have they're own interpretations with her. Maybe once the translations are out more might make sense. I won't say its rejection they're feeling coz I think the mood would have been darker and I think confetti isn't the best way to describe a heart break. (Please add on anyone) they're so much going and this is just first impressions😅😁

author: @shouldnthave5153
text:
ATTENTION ALL CARATSBecause seventeen's comeback is happening real soon, let's make sure we don't make the same mistakes again in order to maximise our chances at winning first place in music show.
1. PLEASE STREAM THE MUSIC VIDEO AT SEVENTEEN'S OFFICIAL YOUTUBE CHANNEL.One of the reason why our pretty u mv views were pretty low was because fans were watching the music video on 1theK's channel. Even though the view in that channel are still counted, it is better to watch it on seventeen's official channel. It will help them out even more. 
2. PLEASE DONT USE IGCONITO WHILE WATCHING MUSIC VIDEO.When you watch mv using incognito tabs, it will take a longer time to process the views so just watch it in a normal tab, remember to clear your history once in a while. To make it easier, just create a short playlist with the MV included in the list.Also try your best to vote for seventeen when they are nominated on music shows. Some shows allow international fans to vote.Lets work hard for our boys. All of us want them to get the recognition they deserve but it won't happen without effort. Carats, fighting!Cr: with-woozi from tumblr
